  "text": "The boundaries in the streamwise direction are less trivial and play a crucial role in selecting the convection pattern for any Γ x = L x /d l . The corresponding boundary conditions are of the enhancing type [CITATION_1] ): buoyancy, which plays a significant role for Bo D = O(1), drives an upward flow near the hot end wall, generating a single localized convection roll. Similarly, buoyancy drives a downward flow near the cold end wall, generating another, much weaker, convection roll. These rolls appear for M a well below the critical value M a c at which convection pattern emerges away from the end walls. The rolls are steady over a wide range of M a and have a horizontal extent of O(d l ). For Γ x 1 and sufficiently low M a, the flow in the core region between these two convection rolls, i.e., for",
